To integrate $\frac{1}{u^3}$, we use the power rule for integration

&#x20; &#x20;

$$
\begin{array}{rl}\int\limits_1^2 \dfrac{1}{u^3}\text{d}u&=\int\limits_1^2 u^{-3} \ \text{d}u
\\\\&= \dfrac{u^{-3+1}}{-3+1} \bigg|_1^2
\\\\&= \dfrac{u^{-2}}{-2} \bigg|_1^2

\end{array}
$$

&#x20;   &#x20;

***

&#x20; &#x20;

**Substitute the bounds:**

&#x20;   &#x20;

$$
\begin{array}{rl}\int\limits_1^2 \dfrac{1}{u^3}\text{d}u&= \dfrac{u^{-2}}{-2} \bigg|_1^2
\\\\&=\left[\dfrac{(2)^{-2}}{-2}\right]-\left[\dfrac{(1)^{-2}}{-2}\right]
\\\\&=\dfrac{1}{-2\cdot2^2}+\dfrac{1}{2\cdot1^2}
\\\\&=-\dfrac{1}{8}+\dfrac{1}{2}
\\\\&=\dfrac{3}{8}
\end{array}

$$

